	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />- We know that reading 2002h clears the VBlank flag. Well, if NMIs are enabled, "reading 2002h near the VBL time suppress the NMI". If I change this thing to "reading 2002h suppress the NMI" still passes through the (old) test ROMs. Is this correct?
<br />
<br />- I ask because the new test ROM fails on nmi_on_timing (5 N) and I don't know why.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
